Subject: A Mineral Build Up in Water Supply
Regarding: A Mineral Build Up in Water Supply
Description:
Hi,
I'm having trouble with my Smart Brew system. Seems like there might be an issue with clogging or something. The water doesnt come out consistently anymore. It sputters and spits water out some of the time. Other times it works just fine. The problem is that I can never count on the coffee being great quality and its affecting the trust of my customers who depend on me to serve them the best cup of coffee every time.  Please help me fix this problem asap.
-claudia

Subject: Checking In: Your Barista Expresso Experience
Description:
Hi Eva Corets,

It’s been two months since you started your journey with Barista Expresso, and I hope you’re loving every cup of coffee!
Here are some additional tips to enhance your espresso-making experience:
  • Milk Frothing: For perfect milk froth, use cold milk and a clean steam wand. Practice makes perfect!
  • Descaling: Regularly descale your machine to prevent mineral buildup and ensure optimal performance.
  • Bean Storage: Store your coffee beans in an airtight container in a cool, dark place to maintain freshness.
Let me know if there’s anything else I can assist you with.

Best regards,
David Mallory
Customer Success Manager

Subject: Enhance Your Coffee Experience with the Café Corto Espresso Machine
Description:
Hi Aurora,

I hope you're doing well! I noticed your recent interest in our Café Corto Espresso Machine and wanted to reach out personally. Given your engagement in our latest campaign, I’d love to share more details about how this machine could elevate your coffee experience.

 

The Café Corto is designed for high performance, offering:
✅ Barista-quality espresso with precise temperature and pressure control
✅ User-friendly operation—perfect for office or commercial settings
✅ Sleek and compact design that fits seamlessly into any space

 

If your team is exploring new coffee solutions, I’d be happy to set up a quick call or demo to discuss how the Café Corto could be a great fit. Let me know when you’re available, or feel free to reply with any questions.

 

Looking forward to hearing your thoughts!

 

Best,
David Mallory
Senior Account Executive | Contoso Coffee
📧 david.mallory@contosocoffee.com | ☕ www.contosocoffee.com

Subject: How’s Your First Month with Barista Expresso?
Description:
Hi Kevin Martin,

I hope you’re enjoying your new Barista Expresso machine and monthly coffee subscription! It’s been a month since you joined us, and I wanted to check in to see how things are going.
Here are a few tips to help you get the most out of your machine:
  • Grind Size: Experiment with different grind sizes to find the perfect balance for your espresso. A finer grind usually results in a richer flavor.
  • Tamping: Ensure you tamp the coffee grounds evenly to achieve consistent extraction.
  • Cleaning: Regularly clean the portafilter and group head to maintain the quality of your espresso.
If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out. We’re here to help!

Best regards,
David Mallory
Customer Success Manager

Subject: Request for additional information and introducing my colleague
Regarding: A Mineral Build Up in Water Supply
Description:
Hi Claudia,

Thank you again for the conversation, I have a request for additional information. The following information will help us, but if it is not possible or inconvenient it will not stop us from finding a solution.
  • When did the problem start
  • Does the problem always occur
  • How do you know the problem is occurring. For example you may hear a grinding sound or a loud drip
  • Have you tried any steps to fix the problem
  • Anything else you have noticed
I also wanted to let you know that I am going to be on vacation for the next week but I want to ensure you that your issue will be worked on by one of my colleagues. I will make sure I review where we are and they will be able to view your email response as well, so please don't worry about a delay because there won't be one! When I get back from vacation I'll be sure to follow-up and confirm your issue was resolved but I am confident you will be back to brewing the worlds best coffee before then!

And I just want to say again, we absolutely appreciate you and look forward to getting this problem solved.

Thank you again!
Enrico Cattaneo
Customer Service Trial

Subject: Three Months with Barista Expresso: How’s It Going?
Description:
Hi Cacilia Viera,

Can you believe it’s already been three months since you joined the Barista Expresso family? I hope your espresso machine and coffee subscription are exceeding your expectations.
Here are a few more tips to keep your espresso game strong:
  • Brewing Temperature: Ensure your machine is at the right temperature before brewing. This helps extract the best flavors from your coffee.
  • Pressure: Check the pressure gauge to ensure it’s within the optimal range for espresso extraction.
  • Maintenance: Keep up with regular maintenance to prolong the life of your machine and maintain coffee quality.
Also, it’s time to start thinking about your coffee subscription renewal. Let’s schedule a call to discuss your current consumption and renewal options.
Looking forward to hearing from you!

Best regards,
David Mallory
Customer Success Manager

Subject: Welcome to the Barista Expresso Family!
Description:
Hi Alex Baker,

I hope you’re enjoying your new Barista Expresso machine and monthly coffee subscription! It’s been a month since you joined us, and I wanted to check in to see how things are going.
Here are a few tips to help you get the most out of your machine:
  • Grind Size: Experiment with different grind sizes to find the perfect balance for your espresso. A finer grind usually results in a richer flavor.
  • Tamping: Ensure you tamp the coffee grounds evenly to achieve consistent extraction.
  • Cleaning: Regularly clean the portafilter and group head to maintain the quality of your espresso.
If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out. We’re here to help!

Best regards,
David Mallory
Customer Success Manager
